extends layouts/_layout.pug

block variables
  - var activePage = 'dashboard';
  - var activeGroup = 'none';

block content
  .app-title
    div
      h1
        i.fa.fa-dashboard
        |  Dashboard
      //-p Smart Pet Feeder

    ul.app-breadcrumb.breadcrumb
      li.breadcrumb-item
        i.fa.fa-home.fa-lg
      li.breadcrumb-item
        a(href='#') Dashboard

  .row
    .col-md-12
      .tile
        h3.tile-title Feed your cat here
        br
        input.form-control(id="foodAmount", type="number", placeholder="Amount of food")
        br
        button.btn.btn-primary(id='feedCatBtn') Click me to feed

  .row
    .col-md-12
      .tile
        h3.tile-title Realtime Food Measure
        .embed-responsive.embed-responsive-16by9
          canvas.embed-responsive-item(id="FoodChart")


  //- .row

    .col-md-6
      .tile
        h3.tile-title Features

        ul
          li Built with Bootstrap 4, SASS and PUG.js
          li Fully responsive and modular code
          li Seven pages including login, user profile and print friendly invoice page
          li Smart integration of forgot password on login page
          li Chart.js integration to display responsive charts
          li Widgets to effectively display statistics
          li Data tables with sort, search and paginate functionality
          li Custom form elements like toggle buttons, auto-complete, tags and date-picker
          li A inbuilt toast library for providing meaningful response messages to user's actions

        p Vali is a free and responsive admin theme built with Bootstrap 4, SASS and PUG.js. It's fully customizable and modular.

        p Vali is is light-weight, expendable and good looking theme. The theme has all the features required in a dashboard theme but this features are built like plug and play module. Take a look at the #[a(href="http://pratikborsadiya.in/blog/vali-admin", target="_blank") documentation] about customizing the theme colors and functionality.

        p.mt-4.mb-4
          a.btn.btn-primary.mr-2.mb-2(href="http://pratikborsadiya.in/blog/vali-admin", target="_blank")
            i.fa.fa-file
            | Docs
          a.btn.btn-info.mr-2.mb-2(href="https://github.com/pratikborsadiya/vali-admin", target="_blank")
            i.fa.fa-github
            | GitHub
          a.btn.btn-success.mr-2.mb-2(href="https://github.com/pratikborsadiya/vali-admin/archive/master.zip", target="_blank")
            i.fa.fa-download
            | Download


    .col-md-6
      .tile
        h3.tile-title Compatibility with frameworks
        p This theme is not built for a specific framework or technology like Angular or React etc. But due to it's modular nature it's very easy to incorporate it into any front-end or back-end framework like Angular, React or Laravel.

        p Go to #[a(href="http://pratikborsadiya.in/blog/vali-admin", target="_blank") documentation] for more details about integrating this theme with various frameworks.

        p The source code is available on GitHub. If anything is missing or weird please report it as an issue on #[a(href="https://github.com/pratikborsadiya/vali-admin", target="_blank") GitHub]. If you want to contribute to this theme pull requests are always welcome.

